wikipedia_page.main: Pete Greenwood (born 23 June 1980) is a British singer-songwriter. He is most well known for his debut album Sirens. Greenwood is also known for his previous work with psychedelic rock band The See See and country rock band The Loose Salute. He has toured in Mojave 3 and Starsailor. Greenwood was born in Morley, Leeds, England and grew up in Headingley.
